{"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/martareinhardtrs/logflow?scriptVersionId=314443781\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"id":"7fcd7b18","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-25T21:45:28.400918Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-25T21:45:28.400666Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.142979Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.14192Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.748686,"end_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.144803+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:28.396117+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["/kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b-it/1/config.json\n","/kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b-it/1/README.md\n","/kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b-it/1/tokenizer.json\n","/kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b-it/1/tokenizer_config.json\n","/kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b-it/1/chat_template.jinja\n","/kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b-it/1/model.safetensors\n","/kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b-it/1/processor_config.json\n","/kaggle/input/models/google/gemma-4/transformers/gemma-4-e4b-it/1/generation_config.json\n"]}],"source":["# This Python 3 environment comes with many helpful analytics libraries installed\n","# It is defined by the kaggle/python Docker image: https://github.com/kaggle/docker-python\n","# For example, here's several helpful packages to load\n","\n","import numpy as np # linear algebra\n","import pandas as pd # data processing, CSV file I/O (e.g. pd.read_csv)\n","\n","# Input data files are available in the read-only \"../input/\" directory\n","# For example, running this (by clicking run or pressing Shift+Enter) will list all files under the input directory\n","\n","import os\n","for dirname, _, filenames in os.walk('/kaggle/input'):\n","    for filename in filenames:\n","        print(os.path.join(dirname, filename))\n","\n","# You can write up to 20GB to the current directory (/kaggle/working/) that gets preserved as output when you create a version using \"Save & Run All\" \n","# You can also write temporary files to /kaggle/temp/, but they won't be saved outside of the current session"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"3296dba3","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.002791,"end_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.150838+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.148047+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["\n","## Logiflow: The Intelligent Bridge for Conscious Commerce\n","The Mission:\n","Logiflow is a real-time information bridge designed to eliminate the gap between local production and final consumption. It empowers seller and producers while fighting waste through transparency and community connection.\n","How it Benefits Everyone:\n","\n","* For Producers & Farmers: Often, fresh produce is lost simply due to a lack of communication channels. Logiflow gives farmers a voice, ensuring their harvest finds a buyer before it's too late.\n","* For Retailers: Instead of seeing inventory as a potential loss, shopkeepers can take proactive control. By identifying near-expiry items, they can trigger instant promotions or list items for donation.\n","* For the Community: When prices drop due to smart logistics, high-quality organic food becomes accessible to everyone. It’s a natural way to support families with tighter budgets without the need for complex bureaucracy.\n","* For Society: It facilitates a seamless path for donations, connecting surplus food directly with those who can distribute it to people in need.\n","\n","The Google tools Factor:\n","Google acts as the \"intelligence\" of the bridge, processing raw inventory data into actionable local insights. It transforms a silent warehouse into a loud, helpful signal for the entire neighborhood.\n","------------------------------\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":2,"id":"d036c2f8","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.158199Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.157678Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.221723Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.220283Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.069741,"end_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.223307+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.153566+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["✅ Database 'logiflow_real.db' initialized with real-world retail data.\n","\n","==================================================\n","USER REQUEST: Show me all organic juices in Sector-C\n","==================================================\n","[Gemma-SQL-Agent] Analyzing NLU for: 'Show me all organic juices in Sector-C'\n","GENERATED SQL: SELECT p.name, i.quantity, i.site, i.sector FROM inventory i JOIN products p ON i.product_id = p.product_id WHERE p.name LIKE '%Juice%' AND i.sector = 'Sector-C';\n","[Gemma-Synthesis-Agent] Synthesizing data into Natural Language...\n","✅ Here is what I found:\n","                name  quantity    site   sector\n","Organic Orange Juice       177 Site-MG Sector-C\n","\n","==================================================\n","USER REQUEST: Which items are expiring in the next 10 days?\n","==================================================\n","[Gemma-SQL-Agent] Analyzing NLU for: 'Which items are expiring in the next 10 days?'\n","GENERATED SQL: SELECT p.name, i.expiry_date, i.quantity FROM inventory i JOIN products p ON i.product_id = p.product_id WHERE i.expiry_date <= date('now', '+10 days');\n","[Gemma-Synthesis-Agent] Synthesizing data into Natural Language...\n","⚠️ **EXPIRATION ALERT**: The following items are expiring soon:\n","- Avocado (Organic): expires on 2026-04-26 (28 units)\n","- Organic Orange Juice: expires on 2026-04-28 (177 units)\n","- Whole Grain Bread: expires on 2026-04-27 (28 units)\n","- Organic Orange Juice: expires on 2026-04-26 (81 units)\n","- Avocado (Organic): expires on 2026-04-25 (23 units)\n","- Organic Orange Juice: expires on 2026-05-02 (109 units)\n","- Avocado (Organic): expires on 2026-04-18 (87 units)\n","- Greek Yogurt: expires on 2026-05-01 (85 units)\n","- Avocado (Organic): expires on 2026-05-04 (148 units)\n","- Greek Yogurt: expires on 2026-04-28 (16 units)\n","- Almond Milk: expires on 2026-04-25 (41 units)\n","- Salted Butter: expires on 2026-04-18 (146 units)\n","- Whole Grain Bread: expires on 2026-04-28 (94 units)\n","\n","\n","==================================================\n","USER REQUEST: What is the total stock count?\n","==================================================\n","[Gemma-SQL-Agent] Analyzing NLU for: 'What is the total stock count?'\n","GENERATED SQL: SELECT SUM(quantity) FROM inventory;\n","[Gemma-Synthesis-Agent] Synthesizing data into Natural Language...\n","📊 The current total stock across all sites is 5656 units.\n"]}],"source":["import sqlite3\n","import pandas as pd\n","import datetime\n","import random\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. DATASET GENERATION (Real-World Style)\n","# ==========================================\n","def initialize_real_data():\n","    conn = sqlite3.connect('logiflow_real.db')\n","    cursor = conn.cursor()\n","\n","    # Create Tables\n","    cursor.execute(\"DROP TABLE IF EXISTS inventory\")\n","    cursor.execute(\"DROP TABLE IF EXISTS products\")\n","\n","    cursor.execute('''CREATE TABLE products (\n","                        product_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n","                        name TEXT,\n","                        category TEXT)''')\n","\n","    cursor.execute('''CREATE TABLE inventory (\n","                        item_id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,\n","                        product_id INTEGER,\n","                        quantity INTEGER,\n","                        site TEXT,\n","                        sector TEXT,\n","                        shelf TEXT,\n","                        expiry_date DATE,\n","                        condition TEXT,\n","                        FOREIGN KEY(product_id) REFERENCES products(product_id))''')\n","\n","    # Mocking Public Retail Data (FMCG Style)\n","    products = [\n","        (1, 'Organic Orange Juice', 'Beverages'),\n","        (2, 'Almond Milk', 'Dairy'),\n","        (3, 'Greek Yogurt', 'Dairy'),\n","        (4, 'Whole Grain Bread', 'Bakery'),\n","        (5, 'Avocado (Organic)', 'Produce'),\n","        (6, 'Salted Butter', 'Dairy'),\n","        (7, 'Oat Milk', 'Beverages'),\n","        (8, 'Dark Chocolate', 'Snacks')\n","    ]\n","    \n","    sites = ['Site-SP', 'Site-RJ', 'Site-MG']\n","    sectors = ['Sector-A', 'Sector-B', 'Sector-C']\n","    conditions = ['new', 'new', 'used', 'new'] # Mix of conditions\n","\n","    cursor.executemany(\"INSERT INTO products VALUES (?,?,?)\", products)\n","\n","    # Generate 50 rows of realistic inventory\n","    inventory_rows = []\n","    for i in range(1, 51):\n","        p_id = random.randint(1, 8)\n","        qty = random.randint(5, 200)\n","        site = random.choice(sites)\n","        sec = random.choice(sectors)\n","        shelf = f\"Shelf-{random.randint(1, 20)}\"\n","        # Random expiry dates: some in past, some in future\n","        days_diff = random.randint(-10, 60)\n","        expiry = (datetime.date.today() + datetime.timedelta(days=days_diff)).isoformat()\n","        cond = random.choice(conditions)\n","        inventory_rows.append((i, p_id, qty, site, sec, shelf, expiry, cond))\n","\n","    cursor.executemany(\"INSERT INTO inventory VALUES (?,?,?,?,?,?,?,?)\", inventory_rows)\n","    conn.commit()\n","    conn.close()\n","    print(\"✅ Database 'logiflow_real.db' initialized with real-world retail data.\")\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. THE INTELLIGENT ENGINE (Gemma Workflow Simulation)\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","class LogiFlowIntelligence:\n","    def __init__(self, db_path):\n","        self.db_path = db_path\n","        self.schema = \"\"\"\n","        Table 'products': product_id (INT), name (TEXT), category (TEXT)\n","        Table 'inventory': item_id (INT), product_id (INT), quantity (INT), \n","                          site (TEXT), sector (TEXT), shelf (TEXT), \n","                          expiry_date (DATE), condition (TEXT)\n","        \"\"\"\n","\n","    def _mock_gemma_text_to_sql(self, user_query):\n","        \"\"\"\n","        In production, this replaces a call to Gemma: \n","        response = gemma.generate(prompt=f\"{self.schema} Query: {user_query}\")\n","        \"\"\"\n","        print(f\"[Gemma-SQL-Agent] Analyzing NLU for: '{user_query}'\")\n","        \n","        # Logic simulating Gemma's reasoning\n","        if \"juice\" in user_query.lower() and \"sector-c\" in user_query.lower():\n","            return \"SELECT p.name, i.quantity, i.site, i.sector FROM inventory i JOIN products p ON i.product_id = p.product_id WHERE p.name LIKE '%Juice%' AND i.sector = 'Sector-C';\"\n","        \n","        elif \"expiring\" in user_query.lower() or \"expiry\" in user_query.lower():\n","            return \"SELECT p.name, i.expiry_date, i.quantity FROM inventory i JOIN products p ON i.product_id = p.product_id WHERE i.expiry_date <= date('now', '+10 days');\"\n","        \n","        elif \"total\" in user_query.lower() and \"stock\" in user_query.lower():\n","            return \"SELECT SUM(quantity) FROM inventory;\"\n","            \n","        else:\n","            return \"SELECT * FROM inventory LIMIT 5;\" # Fallback\n","\n","    def _mock_gemma_synthesis(self, query, dataframe):\n","        \"\"\"\n","        In production, this replaces:\n","        response = gemma.generate(prompt=f\"Translate this data to human: {dataframe}\")\n","        \"\"\"\n","        print(f\"[Gemma-Synthesis-Agent] Synthesizing data into Natural Language...\")\n","        if dataframe.empty:\n","            return \"I searched the database, but I couldn't find any items matching your request.\"\n","        \n","        if \"SUM\" in query:\n","            total = dataframe.iloc[0, 0]\n","            return f\"📊 The current total stock across all sites is {total} units.\"\n","        \n","        if \"expiry\" in query.lower():\n","            items = dataframe.to_dict('records')\n","            msg = \"⚠️ **EXPIRATION ALERT**: The following items are expiring soon:\\n\"\n","            for item in items:\n","                msg += f\"- {item['name']}: expires on {item['expiry_date']} ({item['quantity']} units)\\n\"\n","            return msg\n","\n","        return f\"✅ Here is what I found:\\n{dataframe.to_string(index=False)}\"\n","\n","    def process_request(self, user_query):\n","        print(f\"\\n{'='*50}\")\n","        print(f\"USER REQUEST: {user_query}\")\n","        print(f\"{'='*50}\")\n","\n","        # 1. Text-to-SQL (Gemma Step 1)\n","        sql_query = self._mock_gemma_text_to_sql(user_query)\n","        print(f\"GENERATED SQL: {sql_query}\")\n","\n","        # 2. Execution (Database Step)\n","        try:\n","            conn = sqlite3.connect(self.db_path)\n","            df = pd.read_sql_query(sql_query, conn)\n","            conn.close()\n","\n","            # 3. Synthesis (Gemma Step 2)\n","            final_answer = self._mock_gemma_synthesis(sql_query, df)\n","            return final_answer\n","\n","        except Exception as e:\n","            return f\"❌ Error executing query: {str(e)}\"\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. RUN THE TEST SUITE\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","initialize_real_data()\n","engine = LogiFlowIntelligence('logiflow_real.db')\n","\n","# Test 1: Specific Entity + Constraint (NLU Test)\n","print(engine.process_request(\"Show me all organic juices in Sector-C\"))\n","\n","# Test 2: Proactive Expiry (Alert Test)\n","print(engine.process_request(\"Which items are expiring in the next 10 days?\"))\n","\n","# Test 3: Aggregation (Reporting Test)\n","print(engine.process_request(\"What is the total stock count?\"))"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"d31462f0","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.003079,"end_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.229302+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.226223+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["\n","## ❤️ Connecting Community & Commerce: A Human-Centric Logistics Solution## The Vision: No Item Left Behind\n","Our project uses Gemma to create a \"Digital Bridge\" between local shopkeepers and their neighbors. The goal is simple but profound: to ensure that no product goes to waste while a person nearby is looking for it.\n","## Empowering the Local Hero (The Small Business Owner)\n","Small retailers and local suppliers are the heart of our community. However, they often struggle with:\n","\n","   1. Invisible Stock: Neighbors don't know what's available on their shelves in real-time.\n","   2. Painful Waste: Watching fresh, organic food go to waste is both a financial and emotional burden.\n","   3. Disconnected Tools: They have the products, but no easy way to tell the \"Google world\" exactly what is ready for pick-up now.\n","\n","## How Gemma Facilitates this Human Connection:\n","\n","* A Real-Time Voice for Sellers: Instead of complex systems, sellers can easily report their actual stock. Gemma acts as the \"translator,\" taking that raw info and making it useful for the community.\n","* The \"Proximity Link\": When a user searches for a basic need, Google doesn't just show a link; it shows a local solution. It says: \"Your neighbor at the corner store has this item fresh and ready for you.\"\n","* Social & Environmental Impact: By identifying items nearing their expiration, Gemma suggests community-first actions:\n","* Affordability: Helping low-income families find quality products at a discount.\n","   * Solidarity: Connecting stores directly with local food banks for seamless donations.\n","\n","## Why this Matters:\n","This is not just a logistics app; it's a Sustainability Bridge. It’s about building a world where technology serves the neighborhood, reduces the environmental footprint of waste, and supports the local economy.\n","\n","\"Gemma helps us turn 'inventory data' into 'community support'. It's about making sure the organic juice from a local producer finds its way to a person's table, not a landfill.\"\n","\n","------------------------------\n","\n","\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"id":"1d7aef41","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.236413Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.236147Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.387525Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.386886Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.163799,"end_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.395891+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.232092+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"model_id":"db03569b53704a0dab6125129f37ee50","version_major":2,"version_minor":0},"text/plain":["VBox(children=(HTML(value='<h2>🛒 Logiflow Intelligence Search Bridge</h2>'), HTML(value='<p>Enter a product to…"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import datetime\n","import ipywidgets as widgets\n","from IPython.display import display, HTML, clear_output\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. DATA SOURCE (High-Fidelity Public Mockup)\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","def generate_public_inventory():\n","    \"\"\"Generates a robust DataFrame mimicking real-world retail data.\"\"\"\n","    products_list = [\n","        (\"Organic Milk\", \"Dairy\"), (\"Fresh Avocado\", \"Produce\"), \n","        (\"Greek Yogurt\", \"Dairy\"), (\"Sourdough Bread\", \"Bakery\"),\n","        (\"Almond Milk\", \"Beverages\"), (\"Red Apples\", \"Produce\"),\n","        (\"Dark Chocolate\", \"Snacks\"), (\"Avocado Toast Kit\", \"Bakery\")\n","    ]\n","    stores = [\"Corner Market\", \"Green Grocer\", \"City SuperMart\", \"Local Pantry\", \"Organic Hub\"]\n","    \n","    data = []\n","    today = datetime.date.today()\n","\n","    for _ in range(60):  # Generate 60 entries\n","        p_name, p_cat = random.choice(products_list)\n","        store = random.choice(stores)\n","        dist = round(random.uniform(0.5, 12.0), 1)\n","        qty = random.randint(0, 50)\n","        price = round(random.uniform(2.5, 15.0), 2)\n","        \n","        # Expiry Date Logic: Some very soon (Zero Waste), some far away\n","        # We'll mix them: 10% chance of being < 3 days\n","        if random.random() < 0.15:\n","            expiry = today + datetime.timedelta(days=random.randint(0, 2))\n","        else:\n","            expiry = today + datetime.timedelta(days=random.randint(5, 30))\n","            \n","        data.append({\n","            \"Product\": p_name,\n","            \"Category\": p_cat,\n","            \"Store_Name\": store,\n","            \"Distance_km\": dist,\n","            \"Stock_Qty\": qty,\n","            \"Expiry_Date\": expiry,\n","            \"Price\": price\n","        })\n","    \n","    return pd.DataFrame(data)\n","\n","# Initialize the global dataset\n","public_inventory = generate_public_inventory()\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. THE AGENTIC ENGINE (Logic Layer)\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","class LogiflowAgent:\n","    def __init__(self, df):\n","        self.df = df\n","\n","    def search_and_format(self, query):\n","        # 1. SEARCH: Filter the dataframe\n","        results = self.df[self.df['Product'].str.contains(query, case=False, na=False)]\n","        \n","        if results.empty or results['Stock_Qty'].sum() == 0:\n","            return self.handle_fallback()\n","\n","        # 2. VALIDATE & TRANSFORM: Build HTML Cards\n","        html_output = \"<h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>📍 Nearby Availability Found:</h3>\"\n","        html_output += \"<div style='display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 15px;'>\"\n","\n","        today = datetime.date.today()\n","\n","        for _, row in results.iterrows():\n","            # Skip items out of stock\n","            if row['Stock_Qty'] <= 0:\n","                continue\n","\n","            # Logic: Zero Waste Check\n","            is_zero_waste = (row['Expiry_Date'] - today).days < 3\n","            discount_price = round(row['Price'] * 0.5, 2)\n","            \n","            # Styling components\n","            badge_color = \"#27ae60\" # Green for Verified\n","            zero_waste_label = \"\"\n","            price_display = f\"${row['Price']:.2f}\"\n","            \n","            if is_zero_waste:\n","                zero_waste_label = f'<div style=\"background-color: #e74c3c; color: white; padding: 4px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 10px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 5px;\">🔥 LOGIFLOW ZERO WASTE DEAL - 50% OFF</div>'\n","                price_display = f'<span style=\"text-decoration: line-through; color: #7f8c8d; font-size: 12px;\">${row['Price']:.2f}</span> <span style=\"color: #e74c3c; font-weight: bold;\">${discount_price:.2f}</span>'\n","\n","            # Card HTML Construction\n","            html_output += f\"\"\"\n","            <div style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px; width: 250px; background-color: white; box-shadow: 2px 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); font-family: sans-serif;\">\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 12px; color: {badge_color}; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 5px;\">✅ {row['Store_Name']} (Verified Today)</div>\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #2c3e50; margin-bottom: 8px;\">{row['Product']}</div>\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 13px; color: #7f8c8d; margin-bottom: 10px;\">📍 {row['Distance_km']} km away</div>\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; color: #2c3e50;\">{price_display}</div>\n","                {zero_waste_label}\n","                <div style=\"margin-top: 10px; font-size: 11px; color: #95a5a6;\">Exp: {row['Expiry_Date']}</div>\n","            </div>\n","            \"\"\"\n","        \n","        html_output += \"</div>\"\n","        \n","        # If all items in results were out of stock\n","        if \"</div>\" in html_output and len(results) > 0 and \"📍\" not in html_output:\n","             return self.handle_fallback()\n","             \n","        return html_output\n","\n","    def handle_fallback(self):\n","        \"\"\"Human-centric fallback for missing items.\"\"\"\n","        return f\"\"\"\n","        <div style=\"padding: 20px; border: 2px dashed #e74c3c; border-radius: 10px; background-color: #fdf2f2; text-align: center; font-family: sans-serif;\">\n","            <h3 style=\"color: #c0392b;\">⚠️ No local stock verified today.</h3>\n","            <p>We couldn't find that item in your immediate area right now.</p>\n","            <a href=\"https://www.google.com/shopping\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"background-color: #3498db; color: white; padding: 10px 20px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: bold;\">Searching global Google Shopping links...</a>\n","        </div>\n","        \"\"\"\n","\n","# Initialize the Agent\n","agent = LogiflowAgent(public_inventory)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. INTERACTIVE INTERFACE (ipywidgets)\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","# UI Elements\n","text_input = widgets.Text(\n","    placeholder='e.g. Organic Milk',\n","    description='Search:',\n","    style={'description_width': 'initial'},\n","    layout=widgets.Layout(width='300px')\n",")\n","\n","search_button = widgets.Button(\n","    description='Find Nearby (Logiflow Bridge)',\n","    button_style='success', # 'success', 'info', 'warning', 'danger' or ''\n","    tooltip='Click to search local inventory',\n","    icon='search',\n","    layout=widgets.Layout(width='250px')\n",")\n","\n","output_area = widgets.Output()\n","\n","# The \"Click\" Event Handler\n","def on_button_clicked(b):\n","    with output_area:\n","        clear_output()\n","        query = text_input.value.strip()\n","        if not query:\n","            print(\"Please enter a product name to search.\")\n","            return\n","        \n","        # Trigger Agent Logic\n","        result_html = agent.search_and_format(query)\n","        display(HTML(result_html))\n","\n","search_button.on_click(on_button_clicked)\n","\n","# Layout arrangement\n","ui = widgets.VBox([\n","    widgets.HTML(\"<h2>🛒 Logiflow Intelligence Search Bridge</h2>\"),\n","    widgets.HTML(\"<p>Enter a product to see real-time verified local availability and Zero Waste deals.</p>\"),\n","    widgets.HBox([text_input, search_button]),\n","    output_area\n","])\n","\n","# Display the UI\n","display(ui)"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"id":"584b09db","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.404254Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.403871Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.507786Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.506958Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.124249,"end_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.523566+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-25T21:45:29.399317+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json":{"model_id":"209f534171f24c099f053e27b578ddfa","version_major":2,"version_minor":0},"text/plain":["VBox(children=(HTML(value='\\n<div style=\"background-color: #2c3e50; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; text-a…"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"}],"source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","import datetime\n","import random\n","import ipywidgets as widgets\n","from IPython.display import display, HTML, clear_output\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 1. DATA LAYER (The Shared Source of Truth)\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","def generate_initial_data():\n","    \"\"\"Generates the starting public dataset.\"\"\"\n","    products_list = [\n","        (\"Organic Milk\", \"Dairy\"), (\"Fresh Avocado\", \"Produce\"), \n","        (\"Greek Yogurt\", \"Dairy\"), (\"Sourdough Bread\", \"Bakery\"),\n","        (\"Almond Milk\", \"Beverages\"), (\"Red Apples\", \"Produce\"),\n","        (\"Dark Chocolate\", \"Snacks\"), (\"Avocado Toast Kit\", \"Bakery\")\n","    ]\n","    stores = [\"Corner Market\", \"Green Grocer\", \"City SuperMart\", \"Local Pantry\", \"Organic Hub\"]\n","    data = []\n","    today = datetime.date.today()\n","\n","    for _ in range(30):\n","        p_name, p_cat = random.choice(products_list)\n","        store = random.choice(stores)\n","        dist = round(random.uniform(0.5, 10.0), 1)\n","        qty = random.randint(5, 50)\n","        price = round(random.uniform(3.0, 12.0), 2)\n","        expiry = today + datetime.timedelta(days=random.randint(5, 30))\n","        data.append({\n","            \"Product\": p_name, \"Category\": p_cat, \"Store_Name\": store,\n","            \"Distance_km\": dist, \"Stock_Qty\": qty, \"Expiry_Date\": expiry,\n","            \"Price\": price, \"Last_Updated\": today, \"Discount\": \"0%\"\n","        })\n","    return pd.DataFrame(data)\n","\n","# Initialize the Shared DataFrame\n","public_inventory = generate_initial_data()\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 2. AGENTIC ENGINE (The Intelligence Layer)\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","class LogiflowAgent:\n","    def __init__(self, df):\n","        self.df = df  # This is a reference to the global DataFrame\n","\n","    def search_and_format(self, query):\n","        \"\"\"USER SIDE: Search and display results.\"\"\"\n","        results = self.df[self.df['Product'].str.contains(query, case=False, na=False)]\n","        \n","        if results.empty or results['Stock_Qty'].sum() == 0:\n","            return self.handle_fallback()\n","\n","        html_output = \"<h3 style='color: #2c3e50;'>📍 Local Availability:</h3><div style='display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 15px;'>\"\n","        today = datetime.date.today()\n","\n","        for _, row in results.iterrows():\n","            # Check for Zero Waste status\n","            days_to_exp = (row['Expiry_Date'] - today).days\n","            is_zero_waste = row['Discount'] != \"0%\" or days_to_exp < 3\n","            \n","            discount_tag = \"\"\n","            if is_zero_waste:\n","                discount_tag = f'<div style=\"background-color: #e74c3c; color: white; padding: 4px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 10px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 5px;\">🔥 LOGIFLOW ZERO WASTE DEAL</div>'\n","\n","            html_output += f\"\"\"\n","            <div style=\"border: 1px solid #ddd; border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px; width: 220px; background-color: white; box-shadow: 2px 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); font-family: sans-serif;\">\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 11px; color: #27ae60; font-weight: bold;\">✅ {row['Store_Name']} (Verified)</div>\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 15px; font-weight: bold; color: #2c3e50; margin: 5px 0;\">{row['Product']}</div>\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 13px; color: #7f8c8d;\">📍 {row['Distance_km']} km away</div>\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #2c3e50; margin-top: 5px;\">${row['Price']:.2f}</div>\n","                {discount_tag}\n","                <div style=\"font-size: 10px; color: #95a5a6; margin-top: 5px;\">Exp: {row['Expiry_Date']}</div>\n","            </div>\n","            \"\"\"\n","        html_output += \"</div>\"\n","        return html_output\n","\n","    def handle_fallback(self):\n","        return \"\"\"<div style=\"padding: 20px; border: 2px dashed #e74c3* ; border-radius: 10px; background-color: #fdf2f2; text-align: center; font-family: sans-serif;\">\n","            <h3 style=\"color: #c0392b;\">⚠️ No local stock verified today.</h3>\n","            <a href=\"https://www.google.com/shopping\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: #3498db;\">Redirecting to Global Google Shopping...</a>\n","            </div>\"\"\"\n","\n","    def update_inventory(self, new_entry: dict):\n","        \"\"\"SELLER SIDE: Upsert logic to update or append data.\"\"\"\n","        global public_inventory\n","        \n","        # Check if (Product + Store) already exists for UPSERT logic\n","        mask = (public_inventory['Product'] == new_entry['Product']) & \\\n","               (public_inventory['Store_Name'] == new_entry['Store_Name'])\n","        \n","        new_row = pd.DataFrame([new_entry])\n","        \n","        if not self.df[mask].empty:\n","            # UPDATE existing\n","            self.df.loc[mask, ['Stock_Qty', 'Price', 'Expiry_Date', 'Last_Updated', 'Discount']] = \\\n","                [new_entry['Stock_Qty'], new_entry['Price'], new_entry['Expiry_Date'], \n","                 new_entry['Last_Updated'], new_entry['Discount']]\n","            return \"✅ Stock Updated Successfully!\"\n","        else:\n","            # APPEND new\n","            self.df = pd.concat([self.df, new_row], ignore_index=True)\n","            return \"✅ New Product Registered & Broadcasted!\"\n","\n","# Initialize Agent with the shared reference\n","agent = LogiflowAgent(public_inventory)\n","\n","# ==========================================\n","# 3. INTERACTIVE UI (Seller & User)\n","# ==========================================\n","\n","# --- USER SIDE WIDGETS ---\n","user_search_input = widgets.Text(placeholder='e.g. Milk', description='🔍 Product:', layout=widgets.Layout(width='